  <Name>k__BackingField: Titus
  fancyName: 
  nickname: tit
  language: English
  lang: eng
  version: New Living Translation
  ver: NLT
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: Greetings from Paul
      content: 'This letter is from Paul, a slave of God and an apostle of Jesus
        Christ. I have been sent to proclaim faith to[COMMENT[0]] those God has chosen
        and to teach them to know the truth that shows them how to live godly lives. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: to strengthen the faith of.
    - title: 
      content: "This truth gives them confidence that they have eternal life, which
        God\u2014who does not lie\u2014promised them before the world began. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And now at just the right time he has revealed this message, which
        we announce to everyone. It is by the command of God our Savior that I have
        been entrusted with this work for him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I am writing to Titus, my true son in the faith that we share.\n\tMay
        God the Father and Christ Jesus our Savior give you grace and peace.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Titus\u2019s Work in Crete"
      content: 'I left you on the island of Crete so you could complete our work
        there and appoint elders in each town as I instructed you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "An elder must live a blameless life. He must be faithful to his wife,[COMMENT[0]]
        and his children must be believers who don\u2019t have a reputation for being
        wild or rebellious. "
      comments:
      - number: '1:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'must have only one wife, '
        - ft: 'or '
          body: 'must be married only once; '
        - ft: 'Greek reads '
          body: must be the husband of one wife.
    - title: 
      content: "A church leader[COMMENT[0]] is a manager of God\u2019s household,
        so he must live a blameless life. He must not be arrogant or quick-tempered;
        he must not be a heavy drinker,[COMMENT[1]] violent, or dishonest with money.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:7a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'An overseer, '
        - ft: 'or '
          body: A bishop.
      - number: '1:7b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: must not drink too much wine.
    - title: 
      content: 'Rather, he must enjoy having guests in his home, and he must love
        what is good. He must live wisely and be just. He must live a devout and
        disciplined life. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He must have a strong belief in the trustworthy message he was taught;
        then he will be able to encourage others with wholesome teaching and show
        those who oppose it where they are wrong.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For there are many rebellious people who engage in useless talk and
        deceive others. This is especially true of those who insist on circumcision
        for salvation. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They must be silenced, because they are turning whole families away
        from the truth by their false teaching. And they do it only for money. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even one of their own men, a prophet from Crete, has said about them,
        \u201CThe people of Crete are all liars, cruel animals, and lazy gluttons.\u201D[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: This quotation is from Epimenides of Knossos.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'This is true. So reprimand them sternly to make them strong in the
        faith. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They must stop listening to Jewish myths and the commands of people
        who have turned away from the truth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Everything is pure to those whose hearts are pure. But nothing is
        pure to those who are corrupt and unbelieving, because their minds and consciences
        are corrupted. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: Such people claim they know God, but they deny him by the way they
        live. They are detestable and disobedient, worthless for doing anything good.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Promote Right Teaching
      content: 'As for you, Titus, promote the kind of living that reflects wholesome
        teaching. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Teach the older men to exercise self-control, to be worthy of respect,
        and to live wisely. They must have sound faith and be filled with love and
        patience.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Similarly, teach the older women to live in a way that honors God.
        They must not slander others or be heavy drinkers.[COMMENT[0]] Instead, they
        should teach others what is good. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: be enslaved to much wine.
    - title: 
      content: 'These older women must train the younger women to love their husbands
        and their children, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'to live wisely and be pure, to work in their homes,[COMMENT[0]] to
        do good, and to be submissive to their husbands. Then they will not bring
        shame on the word of God.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some manuscripts read '
          body: to care for their homes.
    - title: 
      content: 'In the same way, encourage the young men to live wisely. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And you yourself must be an example to them by doing good works of
        every kind. Let everything you do reflect the integrity and seriousness of
        your teaching. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Teach the truth so that your teaching can\u2019t be criticized. Then
        those who oppose us will be ashamed and have nothing bad to say about us.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Slaves must always obey their masters and do their best to please
        them. They must not talk back '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'or steal, but must show themselves to be entirely trustworthy and
        good. Then they will make the teaching about God our Savior attractive in
        every way.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the grace of God has been revealed, bringing salvation to all
        people. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And we are instructed to turn from godless living and sinful pleasures.
        We should live in this evil world with wisdom, righteousness, and devotion
        to God, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'while we look forward with hope to that wonderful day when the glory
        of our great God and Savior, Jesus Christ, will be revealed. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He gave his life to free us from every kind of sin, to cleanse us,
        and to make us his very own people, totally committed to doing good deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You must teach these things and encourage the believers to do them.
        You have the authority to correct them when necessary, so don\u2019t let
        anyone disregard what you say."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Do What Is Good
      content: 'Remind the believers to submit to the government and its officers.
        They should be obedient, always ready to do what is good. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They must not slander anyone and must avoid quarreling. Instead,
        they should be gentle and show true humility to everyone.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Once we, too, were foolish and disobedient. We were misled and became
        slaves to many lusts and pleasures. Our lives were full of evil and envy,
        and we hated each other. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But\u2014\n\tWhen God our Savior revealed his kindness and love, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'he saved us, not because of the righteous things we had done, but
        because of his mercy. He washed away our sins, giving us a new birth and
        new life through the Holy Spirit.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: He saved us through the washing of regeneration and renewing of the
            Holy Spirit.
    - title: 
      content: 'He generously poured out the Spirit upon us through Jesus Christ
        our Savior. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Because of his grace he made us right in his sight and gave us confidence
        that we will inherit eternal life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is a trustworthy saying, and I want you to insist on these teachings
        so that all who trust in God will devote themselves to doing good. These
        teachings are good and beneficial for everyone.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not get involved in foolish discussions about spiritual pedigrees[COMMENT[0]]
        or in quarrels and fights about obedience to Jewish laws. These things are
        useless and a waste of time. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: spiritual genealogies.
    - title: 
      content: 'If people are causing divisions among you, give a first and second
        warning. After that, have nothing more to do with them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For people like that have turned away from the truth, and their own
        sins condemn them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Final Remarks and Greetings"
      content: 'I am planning to send either Artemas or Tychicus to you. As soon
        as one of them arrives, do your best to meet me at Nicopolis, for I have
        decided to stay there for the winter. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do everything you can to help Zenas the lawyer and Apollos with their
        trip. See that they are given everything they need. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Our people must learn to do good by meeting the urgent needs of others;
        then they will not be unproductive.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Everybody here sends greetings. Please give my greetings to the believers\u2014all
        who love us.\n\tMay God\u2019s grace be with you all."
      comments: []
